Connector catalog

Kafka Connect is a framework for connecting Kafka to external systems. It uses source connectors to move data into Kafka, and sink connectors to move data out of Kafka.

The connector catalog contains a list of connectors that are supported either by IBM or the community:

  • IBM supported: Support is provided by IBM for customers with a support entitlement for IBM Cloud Pak for Integration. Raise any issues through the official IBM support channel. IBM will investigate, identify, and provide a fix when possible.
  • Community supported: Each community connector is subject to its own set of license terms and not supported by IBM. Raise issues through the community support links provided for each connector.

Find out more about Kafka Connect

Source connector: produces data into Kafka or Event Streams

Diffusion

Diffusion source connector enables streaming of data stored in Kafka to endpoints like web browsers, mobile apps, and IoT devices, reliably and at scale.

Get help

For more information about configuring and using the connector, see the documentation.
